# ğŸ“Š Brazilian E-Commerce Data Analysis Project

This project analyzes a real-world dataset from a Brazilian e-commerce platform (Olist) to uncover business insights such as customer behavior, sales trends, delivery performance, and more. The analysis uses **Python (Pandas, SQL), Power BI**, and **PostgreSQL** for a complete data analytics workflow.

---

## ğŸ“ Dataset

The dataset is sourced from [Olist's public dataset on Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/olistbr/brazilian-ecommerce), which includes:

- Customers
- Orders
- Order items
- Payments
- Reviews
- Products
- Sellers
- Product category translations
- Geolocation

These tables were merged and cleaned for analytical purposes.

---

## ğŸ“Œ Objectives

- Clean and prepare raw data for analysis
- Perform SQL-based exploratory data analysis (EDA)
- Calculate KPIs like revenue, order value, and customer retention
- Visualize insights using Power BI dashboards
- Draw actionable business conclusions from the data

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Tools & Technologies

- **Python (Pandas, NumPy)**
- **PostgreSQL (pgAdmin for SQL queries)**
- **Power BI** for interactive dashboards
- **Jupyter Notebook** for scripting and analysis

---

## ğŸ“Š Key Metrics Analyzed

- Total Sales & Monthly Trends
- Customer Segments & Repeat Purchases
- Product Category Performance
- Review Score Distribution
- Late Delivery Rate
- Payment Type Analysis
- Geographical Distribution of Orders

